<subSubSection id="738F518DFFC13E18FF51FA65FBFD6097" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3B2A0206FFC13E18FF51FA65FBFD6097" blockId="91.[151,1437,1448,1943]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FF51FA65FED960B3" bold="true" box="[151,276,1448,1475]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Face and gena entirely yellowish-orange, frons black. Fore and mid legs entirely yellowish-orange. Thorax black. Abdomen orangeish-brown. Hind leg simple. Body length: 
<quantity id="FC6DAFE3FFC13E18FC15FA01FBE16097" box="[979,1068,1484,1511]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="5.1">5.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="738F518DFFC13E18FF01FA3DFB516393" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph id="3B2A0206FFC13E18FF01FA3DFDFB637B" blockId="91.[151,1437,1448,1943]" box="[199,566,1520,1547]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FF01FA3DFE72637B" bold="true" box="[199,447,1520,1547]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Description: MALE:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B2A0206FFC13E18FF01F9D9FB516393" blockId="91.[151,1437,1448,1943]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FF01F9D9FE5A635F" bold="true" box="[199,407,1556,1583]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
FEMALE: 
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FE96F9D9FE43635F" bold="true" box="[336,398,1556,1583]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Head</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
Vertex frons and occiput black, face and gena yellowish-orange. Head shining, free of pollinosity. Face and eye sparsely yellow pilose. Vertex yellow pilose. Antenna entirely yellowish-orange. 
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FAFBF9F5FA516323" bold="true" box="[1341,1436,1592,1619]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FAFBF9F5FA5E6323" bold="true" box="[1341,1427,1592,1619]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Thorax</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
Thorax black, shining, pollinosity free. Fore and mid leg entirely yellowish-orange. Hind femur and tibia orangeishbrown, hind tarsomeres yellow. Hind femur unmodified, with only a few weak, black setulae apicoventrally. Thorax entirely yellow pilose. Halter yellow. Calypter pale. Wing colourless, entirely microtrichose. 
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FB66F969FAD563CF" bold="true" box="[1184,1304,1700,1727]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FB66F969FAC363CF" bold="true" box="[1184,1294,1700,1727]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Abdomen</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
Abdominal sclerites orangeish-brown. Tergites white pilose. Sternites white pilose. Sternite 1 pollinose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="738F518DFFC13E18FF01F920FA9162E7" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3B2A0206FFC13E18FF01F920FE6F623F" blockId="91.[151,1437,1448,1943]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FF01F920FE9F6277" bold="true" box="[199,338,1773,1799]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="FC957985FFC13E18FD87F920FD1D6277" authorityName="Young &amp; Skevington &amp; Steenis" authorityYear="2020" box="[577,720,1773,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Psilota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthostoma">
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FD87F920FD1D6277" box="[577,720,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">xanthostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ consists of 
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FC9FF920FC686277" box="[857,933,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">xantho</emphasis>
, derived from the Latin “xanthous”, meaning “yellow”, and 
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FEFCF8DFFEB0625B" box="[314,381,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">stoma</emphasis>
, meaning “hole”, or mouth. This is in reference to the yellow face, gena, and “mouth” area of 
<taxonomicName id="FC957985FFC13E18FF51F8FBFE8F623F" authority="Young &amp; Skevington &amp; Steenis, 2020" authorityName="Young &amp; Skevington &amp; Steenis" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,322,1845,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Psilota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthostoma" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FF51F8FBFE8F623F" box="[151,322,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">P. xanthostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="09E1DE14FFC13E18FE8FF8F8FE6F623F" bold="true" box="[329,418,1845,1871]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="12D2636FFFC13E18FE8FF8F8FE6F623F" box="[329,418,1845,1871]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
